<task id="SPE-014" project="SDAP SPE Admin App">
  <metadata>
    <title>Create Container Endpoint</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>2h</estimated-effort>
    <tags>bff-api, api, graph, phase-1</tags>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <dependencies>SPE-013, SPE-007</dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Implement the Create Container endpoint so administrators can provision new SPE containers through the admin UI. This endpoint must validate input, create the container via Graph API, and record the action in the audit log.</prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET developer familiar with Minimal APIs and Microsoft Graph</role>
  <goal>A working POST endpoint that creates a new container in SharePoint Embedded via Graph API, with input validation and audit logging.</goal>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Use Minimal API endpoint pattern — no controllers, no Azure Functions.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Use endpoint filters for authorization — no global auth middleware.</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-definition.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/graph-sdk-v5.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <context>
    <background>Creating containers is a core admin operation. Each container belongs to a container type (identified via configId). The request must include displayName and optionally description. The audit log (sprk_speauditlog) must record who created the container, when, and what was created.</background>
  </context>
  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Define request model">Create a CreateContainerRequest record with displayName (required) and description (optional) properties.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Implement POST endpoint">Add POST /api/spe/containers?configId={id} to ContainerEndpoints.cs that validates the request body, calls SpeAdminGraphService to create the container via Graph API.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Add input validation">Validate displayName is not empty/whitespace and does not exceed max length. Return 400 with ProblemDetails on validation failure.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Audit log creation">After successful container creation, write an audit log entry to sprk_speauditlog via Dataverse with category "ContainerCreated", details of the new container, and the acting user.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Test endpoint">Verify container is created in SPE, audit log entry exists, and validation rejects invalid input.</step>
  </steps>
  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Endpoints/SpeAdmin/ContainerEndpoints.cs</output>
  </outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">POST /api/spe/containers?configId={id} creates a container in SharePoint Embedded via Graph API.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Missing or empty displayName returns 400 Bad Request.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Successful creation writes an audit log entry to sprk_speauditlog with category "ContainerCreated".</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Response includes the newly created container's ID and details.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
